<Project>
  <ItemGroup>
    <CompilerVisibleProperty Include="QuarrySqlManifestPath" />
    <CompilerVisibleProperty Include="ProjectDir" />
    <CompilerVisibleProperty Include="InterceptorsNamespaces" />
    <CompilerVisibleProperty Include="QuarryInterceptorsNamespaces" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <!-- QuarryInterceptorsNamespaces is a pipe-delimited mirror of InterceptorsNamespaces
       exposed to analyzers so the QRY044 analyzer can validate that the consumer's
       QuarryContext namespace is opted into the interceptors feature.

       Roslyn's editorconfig key-value regex truncates values at the first `;` (it
       treats `;…` as an inline comment), so reading the raw `InterceptorsNamespaces`
       property back from `build_property.*` fails the moment the list has more than
       one entry. `|` isn't a legal C# namespace character, so the `;` → `|`
       substitution is lossless and survives Roslyn's parser intact. The analyzer
       prefers this property and falls back to the raw one only when this one is
       absent.

       Computed in a target (not a top-level PropertyGroup) so the `.Replace` is
       deferred until after every upstream .props / csproj / .targets contribution
       to $(InterceptorsNamespaces) has folded in. `GenerateMSBuildEditorConfigFileCore`
       is an internal Roslyn SDK target in Microsoft.Managed.Core.targets; the
       editorconfig file isn't Public MSBuild contract so the name could change in a
       future SDK. If that happens QRY044 will silently fall back to the legacy path
       (i.e. revert to the original bug shape on the affected inputs). Low likelihood
       — the target has existed since .NET 5 and is widely depended on by source
       generator ecosystems — but worth noting in case diagnostics regress after an
       SDK upgrade.

       Mirrored in Quarry.targets so consumers who install Quarry without Quarry.Generator
       still get the alt property; the two targets compute identical values from
       identical inputs. -->
  <Target Name="_QuarryComputeInterceptorsNamespaces"
          BeforeTargets="GenerateMSBuildEditorConfigFileCore">
    <PropertyGroup>
      <QuarryInterceptorsNamespaces>$(InterceptorsNamespaces.Replace(';', '|'))</QuarryInterceptorsNamespaces>
    </PropertyGroup>
  </Target>
</Project>
